  "prompt": "What is the meaning of Hindi word \u2018\u092d\u0947\u0926\u092d\u093e\u0935\u2019 (Bhedbhaav)?",
  "response": "The Hindi word **'\u092d\u0947\u0926\u092d\u093e\u0935' (Bhedbhaav)** translates to **\"discrimination\"** in English. It refers to the unfair or prejudicial treatment of individuals or groups based on characteristics such as:\n\n- **Caste**\n- **Religion**\n- **Gender**\n- **Race**\n- **Age**\n- **Disability**\n- **Nationality**\n\n**Examples of \u092d\u0947\u0926\u092d\u093e\u0935 (Bhedbhaav):**\n- **Gender Discrimination:** Treating someone unfairly because they are male or female.\n- **Racial Discrimination:** Making assumptions or decisions based on a person's race.\n- **Age Discrimination:** Preferring younger or older individuals for jobs or opportunities solely based on their age.\n\n**In Summary:**\n\u092d\u0947\u0926\u092d\u093e\u0935 (Bhedbhaav) denotes any behavior or policy that results in unequal treatment of people based on inherent or socially constructed differences, leading to inequality and injustice in various aspects of society.",
